                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>Lacquered Persian binding with, on the front, a scene showing the presentation of a book to an enthroned princely figure while musicians play and dance, and, on the back, horeseman shooting arrows at a target on the top of a tall mask to the accompaniment of drummers. Many of the figures wear the tall early Safavid taj. The inside covers decorated with designs of birds and flowers in gold, red and black. Flap and back with tooling, probably later additions. Kept in a modern case. Some fragments from the old binding in the same box.</p>
                  </bindingDesc>
